<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be high as a kite • fly one’s kite high</xh5><p> <i>be high as a kite</i>—(sl.) 1. be very excited or exhilarated: I <u>was as high as a kite</u> and full of the joys of spring. The day was good and getting better.... 2. be very drunk or affected by drugs: When I put you to bed you <u>were high as a kite</u> on vodka.</p><p> <i>fly one’s kite high—</i>have high ambitions: Those who <u>fly their kite too high</u> may come to grief.</p> </entry>
